The paper presents a neuromorphic spiking neural network model for obstacle avoidance in unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), which incorporates spiking frequency adaptation and synaptic plasticity mechanisms. The paper also proposes the use of optimization techniques to optimize the parameter space and investigate the use of self-adaptive differential evolution (DE) to ameliorate the difficulties of finding appropriate input parameters for the DE technique. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses a neuromorphic dynamic vision sensor (DVS) and incorporates computer vision techniques, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the third likely category. The paper also deals with control and optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Learning) as the fourth and fifth likely categories, respectively.
